smiddle>  Art tutorial site recruiting editors and contributors</span><hr size=1> Hi there!<br>
<br>
This note has been posted in several places, has been sanctioned by Spike and is in regards to a website I help run called the Anime Art Academy,  located at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://aaacad.cjb.net">aaacad.cjb.net</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> (or alternatively <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.arwenian.net/AAA">www.arwenian.net/AAA</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ).<br>
<br>
--------- <br>
<br>
Yup. <br>
<br>
I've recently gotten a full time job and as it is, hardly have time to maintain my own website, let alone three. On top of that, I've also been recieving various commission requests that are higher on my priority list (at the moment) than website maintenance for the AAA. Sad but true. <br>
<br>
It's been more than three years since I first came to the AAA crew and while I don't intend to leave entirely, I understand (and hope you as readers do too) that there must be an end to everything at some point in time and that one commitment to a website should not ultimately limit what one wishes to do as an individual. As a result, I hope to step back and place the AAA on my backburner for a while, acting more as an editor than a copygirl, while looking for suitable contributors and web designers to fill the void. <br>
<br>
For the moment, I am looking for people to fill the following positions: <br>
<br>
Editor of Tutorials - responsible for updating the main tutorial page, on and off-site tutorial listings, featured tutorial archives, assigning and editing tutorials to/from contributing staff. Requires demonstratable artistic ability, talent for understanding and being able to edit articles written in the English language. Knowledge of HTML is a MUST. Artistic experience of at least 2-3 years is preferred. <br>
<br>
Editor of Help - responsible for managing the message board, oekaki and chat room, seeing that content in these three areas is kept within a reasonable amount of sanity/decency. Does not require artistic ability, but artistic appreciation and ability to successfully moderate these areas is a MUST. Individuals for this position must be mature and be able to communicate their thoughts clearly using the English language. <br>
<br>
Editor of Features - responsible for updating the main 'Features' page, assigning and editing anime art-related articles to/from contributing staff (including articles for Art tool of the month), updating the articles and art tool of the month page. BW Bin responsibilities for the moment are to remain in the capable hands of Kitchenman/Willy Baka. <br>
<br>
Contributors - Will be responsible for articles assigned by the editors or themselves by a specified deadline. May include articles for tutorial, art-related or art tool of the month sections. Requires individuals with a passion for anime/manga styled art as well as art in general, with demonstratable artistic ability. Talent for understanding and writing articles written in the English language is a MUST. Knowledge of HTML is not needed, but is an asset. All articles must be submitted either in HTML or as a .txt file. <br>
<br>
Web Design and Implementation - As I will be vacating this position, the AAA will require an individual who is willing to ensure the consistency and structure of the website as a whole. New web designs created by a person in this position are welcome, but shall only be implemented if the person in this position implements the work him/herself. Requires demonstratable ability to create and manipulate HTML, CSS and SSI code. Knowledge of PHP is an asset. Interested individuals must be willing to make at least a 6 month commitment to this project. <br>
<br>
Candidates for these positions should contact me as soon as possible at my personal email address (fc@artmail.org) with the following information: <br>
<br>
- Full Name <br>
- Online Handle <br>
- Legitimate email address <br>
- A link to artwork, example of writing ability or HTML expertise (depending on which position you are aiming for) <br>
- Position you are looking for. <br>
- Why you think you are suitable for this position<br>
<br>
I will start accepting applications for contributing staff AFTER I get confirmed individuals for each Editorial position. <br>
<br>
Only serious offers will be considered. Please do not send emails with attachments of over 100kb. I will not read them. If you have samples that exceed this size but no webpage, please email me first and I will provide you with information on where to upload it for my perusal. <br>
<br>
---------- <br>
Thanks for your attention and patience  <br>
<br>
FC <br>
fc@artmail.org / fyrelyzard@hotmail.com <br>
